<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0489 </DOCNO><TEXT>Recent progress in the development of computers, television systems, x-rayintensifiers, and digital electronic storage devices has permitted areassessment of intravenous angiography in the evaluation of vascularstructures. The images obtained with digital subtraction angiographyare comparable to those of conventional angiography. Its accuracy andsafety have been documented in comparative studies with intracranialand extracranial carotids, abdominal aorta, renal arteries, and cardiacsystems.</TEXT></DOC>